@node Shared session behavior
@section Shared session behavior

@vindex ai-agent-protect-buffers
@vindex ai-agent-alert-on-ready
@vindex ai-agent-alert-style
@vindex ai-agent-alert-sound
@vindex ai-agent-alert-sound-player
@vindex ai-agent-backtrace-file
@vindex ai-agent-sync-theme
@vindex ai-agent-sigwinch-delay
The user option @code{ai-agent-protect-buffers} is a boolean that defaults to @code{t}. When enabled, killing a live AI session buffer prompts for confirmation through @code{ai-agent-protect-buffer}. Buffers whose processes have already exited are allowed to die without the prompt.

The user option @code{ai-agent-alert-on-ready} is a boolean that defaults to @code{nil}. When enabled, backend notification handlers can call @code{ai-agent-notify} to emit visual and/or audible alerts when a session is waiting for input. @code{ai-agent-alert-style} selects @code{visual}, @code{sound}, or @code{both}; it defaults to @code{both}. @code{ai-agent-alert-sound} defaults to @code{nil}; set it to a sound file to enable sound alerts. @code{ai-agent-alert-sound-player} optionally names an external sound player when Emacs sound support is unavailable.

The user option @code{ai-agent-backtrace-file} controls where @code{ai-agent-save-backtrace}, @code{ai-agent-claude-debug-backtrace}, and @code{ai-agent-codex-debug-backtrace} write Emacs backtraces. It defaults to a file in @code{temporary-file-directory}.

The user option @code{ai-agent-sync-theme} is a boolean that defaults to @code{nil}. When enabled, theme changes in Emacs are persisted through each registered backend's theme-sync handler. This updates configuration files for new or restarted CLI sessions without sending theme commands into active terminal conversations.

The user option @code{ai-agent-sigwinch-delay} is a number of seconds and defaults to @samp{0.5}. It controls how long @code{ai-agent-fix-rendering} waits before sending @samp{SIGWINCH} to a terminal process. Increase it if an AI CLI reads the terminal size before the @samp{eat} window has settled.

Snippet helpers use @samp{yasnippet} and @samp{consult-yasnippet} only when those optional packages are loaded.

