@vindex ai-agent-codex-exec-sandbox-mode
@vindex ai-agent-codex-exec-skip-git-repo-check
@vindex ai-agent-codex-debug-backtrace-model
@vindex ai-agent-codex-debug-backtrace-backend
The Codex backend options control account selection, handoff, skill discovery, non-interactive execution, project auditing, and backtrace debugging. @code{ai-agent-codex-accounts} is an alist of account names to Codex home directories, and @code{ai-agent-codex-account-file} stores the selected account across Emacs sessions. Account homes keep credentials such as @samp{auth.json} separate, while shared Codex state such as @samp{config.toml}, @samp{hooks.json}, skills, sessions, and @samp{history.jsonl} is symlinked from @samp{~/.codex/} so hooks, skills, project trust, and chat history remain available after switching accounts. Use @code{ai-agent-codex-select-account} or the Codex account infix in @code{ai-agent-menu} to switch accounts before starting a new session. @code{ai-agent-codex-handoff-file} defaults to a file in @code{temporary-file-directory} and is read by @code{ai-agent-codex-handoff} after the Codex handoff skill writes next-session instructions.

@code{ai-agent-codex-skill-directories} is a list of additional directories scanned for Codex skills. The backend also scans standard Codex skill locations and project-local skill directories. @code{ai-agent-codex-audit-skills} defaults to the code, design, and interpretability audit skills, while @code{ai-agent-codex-audit-project-directories} stores completion candidates for the audit directory prompt.

@code{ai-agent-codex-exec-approval-policy}, @code{ai-agent-codex-exec-sandbox-mode}, and @code{ai-agent-codex-exec-skip-git-repo-check} configure the non-interactive Codex calls used by skill and audit workflows. The approval policy is passed as a top-level Codex CLI option before the @samp{exec} subcommand, while the sandbox and repository-check options are passed to @samp{codex exec} itself.

@code{ai-agent-codex-debug-backtrace-model} and @code{ai-agent-codex-debug-backtrace-backend} configure the @samp{gptel} request used by @code{ai-agent-codex-debug-backtrace} to identify likely culprit packages from an Emacs backtrace.

