@findex ai-agent-fix-rendering
@findex ai-agent-disable-scrollback-truncation
@findex ai-agent-snippet-tab
The command @code{ai-agent-menu} opens the unified transient menu. It includes shared entries for session switching, waiting-session jumps, handoff, restart, exit, skill execution, project audit, backtrace debugging, alert toggles, and terminal maintenance. Backend modules append their own suffixes to the same menu when loaded.

The command @code{ai-agent-start-or-switch} is the main entry point. If no sessions exist, it starts a new session through the selected backend. If sessions already exist, it opens the session switcher. Sessions receive stable home-row keys where possible and display backend icons next to their labels.

The command @code{ai-agent-run-skill} discovers skills from every loaded backend that implements skill discovery. It disambiguates same-named skills by backend label, prompts for declared arguments when a skill frontmatter requests them, and dispatches the invocation to the selected backend. Claude and Codex backends scan global and project-local programmatic skill directories, using both @code{project-current} and nearby tool directories as project-root signals, so batch-only skills can be run from this command without being loaded into ordinary interactive agent sessions.

The command @code{ai-agent-post-push-ci} runs the @code{post-push-ci} skill through the
selected backend with @samp{--no-push --commit HEAD}. Use it after a push has
already happened and you want an agent to inspect GitHub Actions failures, fix
the root cause, and continue the authorized CI closeout loop.

The commands @code{ai-agent-handoff}, @code{ai-agent-audit-project}, @code{ai-agent-debug-backtrace}, @code{ai-agent-exit}, and @code{ai-agent-restart} resolve a backend from the current session buffer or by prompting. This lets the same keybinding operate on Claude or Codex sessions without separate wrapper commands.

@code{ai-agent-before-exit-functions} can delay @code{ai-agent-exit} for cleanup work.
Each function receives the resolved backend and session buffer; returning nil
aborts the exit.

Set @code{ai-agent-before-exit-skill-name} and
@code{ai-agent-before-exit-skill-directories} to submit an interactive skill before
exiting matching sessions. @code{ai-agent-run-skill-before-exit} uses
@code{ai-agent-skill-command-prefix-alist} so Claude sessions receive slash commands
and Codex sessions receive dollar-prefixed skill commands, then submits the
command and delays exit until the next @code{ai-agent-exit} call.

