The Claude commands expose workflows that are specific to Claude Code. @code{ai-agent-claude-start-or-switch} starts Claude under the selected account or opens the unified switcher. @code{ai-agent-claude-select-account} persists an account choice, and @code{ai-agent-claude-init-account} prepares a new account directory with shared configuration files and symlinks.

@code{ai-agent-claude-run-skill}, @code{ai-agent-claude-batch-todos}, and @code{ai-agent-claude-send-todo-at-point} use non-interactive or interactive Claude sessions to run structured work. Batch TODO processing extracts Org headings, formats each heading and body as a prompt, runs entries sequentially, and records a summary buffer. Project audits refuse to auto-commit unless the target git worktree is clean before the audit starts.

@code{ai-agent-claude-create-branch} creates a new Claude branch from the current session. With isolated branching it creates a git worktree under @code{ai-agent-claude-fork-worktree-directory} and links the branch session metadata into that project. @code{ai-agent-claude-switch-branch} displays the branch tree and switches to, or resumes, the selected session.

The setup command @code{ai-agent-claude-setup-config} ensures that Claude's statusline, Stop hook, and Notification hook are present in @samp{~/.claude/settings.json}. The backend does not run setup automatically when loaded; run the setup command explicitly when installing or repairing hook configuration.

@node Codex commands
@section Codex commands

@findex ai-agent-codex-start-or-switch
@findex ai-agent-codex-select-account
@findex ai-agent-codex-run-skill
@findex ai-agent-codex-audit-project
@findex ai-agent-codex-debug-backtrace
@findex ai-agent-codex-handoff
@findex ai-agent-codex-restart
@findex ai-agent-codex-exit
@findex ai-agent-codex-resume
@findex ai-agent-codex-fork
@findex ai-agent-codex-setup-kill-on-exit
The Codex commands mirror the shared workflows for the Codex CLI@. @code{ai-agent-codex-start-or-switch} starts Codex under the selected account when no Codex sessions exist, otherwise it opens the shared switcher. @code{ai-agent-codex-select-account} persists an account choice by name and applies it to new interactive sessions and non-interactive @samp{codex exec} runs. @code{ai-agent-codex-run-skill} runs a skill non-interactively with @samp{codex exec}, using local skill metadata when available and falling back to a slash invocation otherwise. Additional programmatic skill directories are configured through @code{ai-agent-codex-programmatic-skill-directories}.

@code{ai-agent-codex-audit-project} prompts for a project directory and runs each configured audit skill sequentially through @samp{codex exec}. @code{ai-agent-codex-debug-backtrace} saves the current Emacs backtrace, asks @samp{gptel} to identify likely packages, and starts a Codex session in the selected package source directory with instructions to fix the bug.

@code{ai-agent-codex-handoff} reads @code{ai-agent-codex-handoff-file}, kills the current Codex buffer, and starts a new session with the handoff prompt. @code{ai-agent-codex-handoff-from-emacsclient} accepts the source buffer name from an @samp{emacsclient} argument, so agent-authored handoff commands can close the requesting session even though Emacs evaluates the form outside that buffer. @code{ai-agent-codex-restart} resumes the current project with @samp{codex resume --last} after killing the old session. @code{ai-agent-codex-resume} and @code{ai-agent-codex-fork} expose the Codex CLI's resume and fork subcommands from the unified menu.

