The function @code{ai-agent-register-backend} registers an AI tool by associating a backend symbol with a property list of buffer predicates, session discovery functions, command senders, and optional command handlers. Backend modules call it at load time. Required keys are validated so the shared session layer can rely on a consistent interface.

@code{ai-agent-display-name} returns a human-readable label for a session buffer. It starts with the project name, adds an instance name when needed to disambiguate duplicates, and lets backends append their own suffixes. The Claude backend uses this to expose branch identity in the modeline and switcher.

@code{ai-agent-parse-skill-frontmatter} reads @samp{SKILL.md} frontmatter shared by Claude and Codex skill runners. It recognizes names, descriptions, argument hints, argument sources, argument choices, defaults, multiplicity, user-invocable flags, and model overrides.

@code{ai-agent-svg-icon} renders SVG strings as inline images, using the current face foreground when the SVG uses @samp{currentColor}. Backends use this for modeline and transient display and can fall back to text abbreviations when SVG rendering is unavailable.

