The Claude and Codex status helpers are intended for modeline integrations such as @samp{doom-modeline}. Claude status functions read the current session status JSON and expose model, cost, context, duration, and token information. Claude usage functions expose account-level utilization returned by the Anthropic usage endpoint. Codex status functions expose the configured model and elapsed session duration.

@node Transient menu
@chapter Transient menu

@findex ai-agent-menu
Backend modules extend @code{ai-agent-menu} through @code{transient-append-suffix} after the core menu is available, first removing their own existing suffixes so reloading does not duplicate or stale-position those entries. The base menu contains shared session, tool, alert, buffer, and option entries. The Claude module appends branch navigation, batch TODOs, TODO sending, log browsing, status polling, Claude account selection, and branch-kill warnings. The Codex module appends Codex resume/fork commands and Codex account selection.

Boolean menu infixes use a shared transient class that toggles the bound variable each time it is invoked. The theme-sync infix additionally calls @code{ai-agent-sync-theme-now} when enabling theme sync, so backend configuration files are updated immediately.

